<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/S0953-7562(96)80214-0" author="Hywel-Jones, NL" journalOrPublisher="Mycological Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" pagination="1065 - 1070" refId="B18" refString="Hywel-Jones, NL, 1996. Akanthomyces on spiders in Thailand. Mycological Research 100 (9): 1065 - 1070, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/S0953-7562(96)80214-0" title="Akanthomyces on spiders in Thailand." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/S0953-7562(96)80214-0" volume="100" year="1996">Hywel-Jones (1996)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="113" type="host">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Host.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
Spider (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luangsa-ard, Hywel-Jones &amp; Spatafora, in Kepler, Luangsa-ard, Hywel-Jones, Quandt, Sung, Rehner, Aime, Henkel, Sanjuan, Zare, Chen, Li, Rossman, Spatafora, Shrestha, IMA Fungus 8: 348" authorityYear="2017" class="Arachnida" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Hevansia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="order">Araneae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blackwall" authorityYear="1841" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Salticidae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="113" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Specimens were found on the underside of dicot leaves of forest plants.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="113" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
Both 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Parahevansia" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Parahevansia koratensis" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" rank="species" species="koratensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Parahevansia koratensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. novoguineensis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="novoguineensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">H. novoguineensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occur on spiders and both produce white mycelium with reddish pigment diffusing in agar media (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/S0953-7562(96)80214-0" author="Hywel-Jones, NL" journalOrPublisher="Mycological Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" pagination="1065 - 1070" refId="B18" refString="Hywel-Jones, NL, 1996. Akanthomyces on spiders in Thailand. Mycological Research 100 (9): 1065 - 1070, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/S0953-7562(96)80214-0" title="Akanthomyces on spiders in Thailand." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/S0953-7562(96)80214-0" volume="100" year="1996">Hywel-Jones 1996</bibRefCitation>
). However, the sporulation of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. novoguineensis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="novoguineensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">H. novoguineensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is produced on media, while no sporulation on media in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="Pa." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pa. koratensis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="koratensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Pa. koratensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was observed. Based on the phylogenetic tree (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. RAxML tree of Hevansia, Jenniferia, Parahevasia, Polystromomyces and related genera in the Cordycipitaceae from a combined ITS, LSU, tef 1, rpb 1 and rpb 2 dataset. Numbers at the major nodes represent Maximum Likelihood Bootstrap (MLB) and Bayesian Posterior Probabilities (BPP). Bold lines in the tree represent 100 % of MLB and 1.00 of BPP. Symbols on the right-hand side correspond to the types of ascospore morphologies found in each genus that are observed in natural specimens of Cordycipitaceae described in Fig. 2." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.91.83091.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719474" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">1</figureCitation>
), NHJ 2662 clustered with the ex-type strain NHJ 666.01 of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="Pa." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pa. koratensis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="koratensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Pa. koratensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The insect host of the strain NHJ 2662 was recorded as a 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="Pa." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Lepidoptera</taxonomicName>
larva. This result shows that 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="Pa." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pa. koratensis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="koratensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Pa. koratensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is parasitic on spiders and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="Pa." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Lepidoptera</taxonomicName>
larva.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
